tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  24,37,"Sabaeans: In ancient times two sects were known by this title:"
  24,38,"See (E. N. 36 of Surah Al-Maidah)."
  24,39,"That is, the fire worshipers of Iran, who believed in two gods, one of light and the other of darknesses, and regarded themselves as the followers of Zoroaster. Their creed and morals were so corrupted by Mazdak that a brother could easily enter into matrimony with his sister."
  24,40,"That is, the mushriks of Arabia and of other countries, who had no special name like those mentioned above."
  24,41,"That is, Allah will pass His judgment on the Day of Resurrection in regard to all the differences and disputes which take place between different people and different religions and will decide which of them was right and which was wrong."
  24,42,"Here all the disputants about Allah have been divided into two main categories in spite of their large numbers."
  24,43,"See (Ayat 50 and E.N. 58 of Surah Ibrahim) for explanation."